Ghana Chooses Trinidad for Gas Joint Venture, Reuters Reports

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-03-17T11:29:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/ghana-chooses-trinidad-for-gas-joint-venture-reuters-reports.html
  Ghana  National Petroleum Corp.
chose  Trinidad and Tobago ’s Natural Gas Co. as its partner in a
project that will transport, process and distribute gas around
the West African nation,  Reuters said .  The joint venture will supply energy to power plants in
Ghana, the news agency said, citing the Caribbean’s island
nation’s Energy Minister Carolyn Seepersad-Bachan.  Ghana has an estimated 800 billion cubic feet of associated
gas from the Jubilee offshore oilfield, Reuters said. Trinidad
and Tobago is the Caribbean’s largest oil and natural gas
producer, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mkhululi Mancotywa in Johannesburg at 
 mmancotywa1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
